{
    "key": "token_value_over_time",
    "name": "Token Value Over Time",
    "category": "Activity",
    "summary": "Scores FET holders based on how long each token lot has been held — using FIFO lot accounting to reward long-term retention over recent acquisitions.",
    "description": "### What it measures\nScores each wallet based on how much FET it still holds and how long those holdings have been retained.\n\n### How scoring works\n- Every incoming transfer creates a separate lot.\n- A lot's value grows linearly from 0% to 100% as it ages toward the maturation threshold.\n- Outgoing transfers consume the oldest lots first (FIFO), so selling recent acquisitions costs less score than selling long-held tokens.\n- The final score is the sum of all remaining normalized lot values at snapshot time.\n\n### Required input\nUpload one JSON file with a top-level `wallets` object mapping each chain to an array of wallet addresses.\n\nExample:\n```json\n{\n  \"wallets\": {\n    \"ethereum\": [\"0x1234567890abcdef1234567890abcdef12345678\"],\n    \"cardano\": [\"addr1q9exampleexampleexampleexampleexampleexample\"]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Resource selection\nSelect one or more token or staking resources to include. Token resources represent the canonical FET token. Staking-contract resources are stored separately in the preset but resolve to the parent FET token during data sync and scoring.\n\n### Data source\nThe algorithm reads indexed token transfer history from the onchain-data dependency for the uploaded wallets only.\n\n### Output files\n- A per-wallet CSV with `wallet_address` and `token_value`.\n- A JSON details file with per-resource and per-lot calculations for auditing.",
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "inputs": [
        {
            "key": "wallets",
            "label": "Wallet Addresses (JSON)",
            "description": "Upload a JSON file with a `wallets` object containing `ethereum` and/or `cardano` wallet address arrays. Only wallets listed here will be scored.",
            "type": "json",
            "required": true,
            "json": {
                "maxBytes": 5242880,
                "schema": "wallet_address_map",
                "rootKey": "wallets",
                "allowedChains": ["ethereum", "cardano"]
            }
        },
        {
            "key": "maturation_threshold_days",
            "label": "Maturation Period (Days)",
            "description": "How many days a token lot must be held before it reaches full value (100%). Lots held for less than this period are credited proportionally.",
            "type": "integer",
            "min": 1,
            "max": 3650,
            "default": 90,
            "step": 1,
            "required": true,
            "uiHint": {
                "widget": "number",
                "suffix": "days",
                "presets": [7, 30, 90, 180, 365]
            }
        },
        {
            "key": "selected_resources",
            "label": "Token Resources to Score",
            "description": "Select one or more FET token or staking contract resources. Each selected resource is tracked separately and resolved to the FET token during sync and scoring.",
